<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1451,589,1019]" box="[136,841,589,616]" pageId="4" pageNumber="271">
<heading bold="true" box="[136,841,589,616]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="4" pageNumber="271" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,841,589,616]" pageId="4" pageNumber="271">
Key for identifying the members of genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Makino &amp; F. Maek. (1935: 596)" authorityName="Makino &amp; F. Maek." authorityPageNumber="596" authorityYear="1935" box="[637,841,589,616]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Chamaegastrodia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="4" pageNumber="271" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[637,841,589,616]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="271">Chamaegastrodia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="271" type="key">
<keyStep pageId="4" pageNumber="271">
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1451,589,1019]" box="[136,1451,622,644]" pageId="4" pageNumber="271">
<keyLead box="[136,1451,622,644]" pageId="4" pageNumber="271">1. Apex of epichile contracted, with rarely entired or only slightly erose margin .................................................................................2</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1451,589,1019]" box="[136,1451,651,673]" pageId="4" pageNumber="271">
<keyLead box="[136,1451,651,673]" pageId="4" pageNumber="271">- Apex of epichile enlarged, partite.......................................................................................................................................................3</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="4" pageNumber="271">
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1451,589,1019]" box="[136,1451,680,702]" pageId="4" pageNumber="271">
<keyLead box="[136,1451,680,702]" pageId="4" pageNumber="271">
2. Lip canoe-shaped, margin wavy; column, with 2 triangular, fleshy wings attached to apex vertically..................... 
<taxonomicName box="[1296,1451,680,701]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Chamaegastrodia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="4" pageNumber="271" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="guidongensis">
<emphasis box="[1296,1451,680,701]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="271">C. guidongensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1451,589,1019]" pageId="4" pageNumber="271">
<keyLead pageId="4" pageNumber="271">
- Lip narrowly ovate to ovate-oblong, apex acute to acuminate; column with 2 dentoid norrow-lanceolate stigmatic processes attached to apex ................................................................................................................................................................. 
<taxonomicName box="[1339,1451,738,759]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Chamaegastrodia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="4" pageNumber="271" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vaginata">
<emphasis box="[1339,1451,738,759]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="271">C. vaginata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="4" pageNumber="271">
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1451,589,1019]" box="[136,1451,766,788]" pageId="4" pageNumber="271">
<keyLead box="[136,1451,766,788]" pageId="4" pageNumber="271">3. Lip Y-shaped, with a deep incision at apex of epichile, saccate at base.............................................................................................4</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1451,589,1019]" box="[136,1451,795,817]" pageId="4" pageNumber="271">
<keyLead box="[136,1451,795,817]" pageId="4" pageNumber="271">- Lip T-shaped, with slightly notched epichile at apex .........................................................................................................................5</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="4" pageNumber="271">
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1451,589,1019]" box="[136,1451,824,846]" pageId="4" pageNumber="271">
<keyLead box="[136,1451,824,846]" pageId="4" pageNumber="271">
4. Lip orange yellow, ca. 16 × 
<quantity box="[480,550,824,845]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="4" pageNumber="271" unit="mm" value="13.0">13 mm</quantity>
, with a pair of elongate introrse lobules at the epichile lobes ................................... 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ormerod" authorityYear="2002" baseAuthorityName="Gagnep." box="[1344,1451,824,845]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Chamaegastrodia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="4" pageNumber="271" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="poilanei">
<emphasis box="[1344,1451,824,845]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="271">C. poilanei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1451,589,1019]" pageId="4" pageNumber="271">
<keyLead pageId="4" pageNumber="271">
- Lip light yellow, 11.2–12.2 × 
<quantity box="[496,593,852,874]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.4" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="5.8" pageId="4" pageNumber="271" unit="mm" value="6.4" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="5.8">5.8–7 mm</quantity>
at apex, absence of a pair of elongate introrse lobules at the epichile lobes ....................... ..................................................................................................................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName authorityName="H. Z. Tian &amp; F. W. Xing" authorityYear="2008" box="[1301,1450,881,903]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Chamaegastrodia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="4" pageNumber="271" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nanlingensis">
<emphasis box="[1301,1450,881,903]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="271">C. nanlingensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="4" pageNumber="271">
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1451,589,1019]" box="[136,1451,910,932]" pageId="4" pageNumber="271">
<keyLead box="[136,1451,910,932]" pageId="4" pageNumber="271">
5. Lip with crisped margin at apex ........................................................................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ormerod" authorityYear="2005" baseAuthorityName="J. Joseph &amp; Abbar." box="[1356,1451,911,932]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Chamaegastrodia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="4" pageNumber="271" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="asraoa">
<emphasis box="[1356,1451,911,932]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="271">C. asraoa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1451,589,1019]" box="[136,1451,939,961]" pageId="4" pageNumber="271">
<keyLead box="[136,1451,939,961]" pageId="4" pageNumber="271">- Lip with entire margin at apex............................................................................................................................................................6</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="4" pageNumber="271">
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1451,589,1019]" box="[136,1451,968,990]" pageId="4" pageNumber="271">
<keyLead box="[136,1451,968,990]" pageId="4" pageNumber="271">
6. Lip mesochile lacking external flanges; anther with 2 narrowly triangular-lanceolate lobes at base, sessile...................... 
<taxonomicName box="[1355,1451,968,989]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Chamaegastrodia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="4" pageNumber="271" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="inverta">
<emphasis box="[1355,1451,968,989]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="271">C. inverta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1451,589,1019]" box="[136,1451,997,1019]" pageId="4" pageNumber="271">
<keyLead box="[136,1451,997,1019]" pageId="4" pageNumber="271">
- Lip mesochile with external flanges; anther lacking basal lobes, attached to column via a short filament................... 
<taxonomicName box="[1319,1451,997,1018]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Chamaegastrodia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="4" pageNumber="271" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="shikokiana">
<emphasis box="[1319,1451,997,1018]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="271">C. shikokiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
</subSubSection>
